data.title: Fujitsu Siemens Computers
data.meta_description: Fujitsu Siemens Computers company contact, support, and additional information about the company.
data.text:
Founded in 1999 as a 50/50 joint venture between Fujitsu Limited of Japan and Siemens of Germany, Fujitsu Siemens Computers was a Japanese and German distributor of information technology. On April 1, 2009, the company became Fujitsu Technology Solutions, following Fujitsu buying out Siemens' share of the company.

Fujitsu Siemens Computers products included handheld and notebook PCs through desktops, servers and storage, and IT data center products and services. Fujitsu Siemens was considered a leader in Green IT, with a presence extending to 170 countries worldwide.

Fujitsu Siemens was the last major Japanese/European computer manufacturer.

Contact information

Fujitsu Siemens Computers is no longer in business and has no e-mail or phone support options. Computer Hope may still be able to assist you with any technical support related questions, but cannot help with any part replacements, warranty, or other company specific related questions.
